job_summary:
At Booking.com, data drives our decisions. Technology is at our core. And innovation is everywhere. But our company is more than datasets, lines of code or A/B tests. We’re the thrill of the first night in a new place. The excitement of the next morning. The friends you make. The journeys you take. The sights you see. And the food you sample. Through our products, partners and people, we can empower everyone to experience the world.
 The Accommodations Technology team is responsible for the design, delivery and reliability of services used by millions of customers and partners on the Web, via mobile and through our extensive APIs. With 28 million places to stay listed on our platform, we work hard to develop products that make it easier for travellers to find the best place to stay in destinations across the globe – in 42 languages and across dozens of currencies.
 You will participate in a global interview process to join one of the teams of the Accommodations Tech Business Unit. If you are successful, you’ll be joining a cross-functional team in the department to innovate and maintain a set of products within our core customer journey.

B. Responsible

Builds and delivers app-wide features, systems and services - regardless of the technology and programming language;
Identifies and escalates flaws and potential issues of app-related infrastructure;
Continuously improves services they own making them more performant, and utilising resources in the most optimised way;
Lead initiatives for improvement of development processes and business opportunities for your team’s product and the company as a whole;
Identify, foster, and proactively help colleagues to grow professionally, taking a significant role in on-boarding new team members;
Represent Booking.com values both in the company and in the external community;
Advocate a collaborative working environment - make “my ideas” into “our ideas”;
Lead, manage and resolve technical or design discussions or conflicts;
Contribute to Booking.com's growth through interviewing, on-boarding, or other recruitment efforts

B. Skilled
We expect our developers to know the ins and outs of the Android framework and to deliver polished products that customers want to use. We need self-starters who are great at solving problems, initiate solutions and discussions and are not afraid of solving challenges due to our large scale.
We have found that people who match the following requirements are the ones who fit us best:

5+ years of experience as a Developer with Java and/or Kotlin and other languages;
At least 3 years of this experience must be from working with the Android SDK;
Strong interaction and design sense, excellent attention to detail;
Experience with automated testing and deployment of Android apps;
Self-motivated to explore new technologies, applications and environments;
Self-starter, highly motivated, team-player.

Bonus points for:

Experience with Google Play Store & Apps Distribution Process;
An approved Play Store app;
Experience with server-driven UI framework development;
Experience working with A/B testing;
You have an intrinsic curiosity in technological innovations and you are always on top of the latest trends.

B.Offered

Living and working in Amsterdam, one of the most cosmopolitan cities in Europe
Contributing to a high scale, complex, world renowned product and seeing real-time impact of your work on millions of travellers worldwide
Working in a fast-paced and performance driven culture
Opportunity to utilize technical expertise, leadership capabilities and entrepreneurial spirit
Promote and drive impactful and innovative engineering solutions
Technical, behavioural and interpersonal competence advancement via on-the-job opportunities, experimental projects, hackathons, conferences and active community participation
Competitive compensation and benefits package and some great added perks of working in the home city of Booking.com

Booking.com is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, colour, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. We strive to move well beyond traditional equal opportunity and work to create an environment that allows everyone to thrive.

 Pre-Employment Screening:  If your application is successful, your personal data may be used for a pre-employment screening check by a third party as permitted by applicable law. Depending on the vacancy and applicable law, a pre-employment screening may include employment history, education and other information (such as media information) that may be necessary for determining your qualifications and suitability for the position.

About XITE It’s our mission to share our passion for music videos with the world and invite people to experience music beyond listening: to see music.  XITE is dedicated to building the best music video experience in the world. Based in Amsterdam, XITE now reaches 100 million households across multiple territories through linear networks, interactive TV apps and on-demand streaming services. The company revolutionized the way audiences experience music videos by allowing viewers to search, like and skip through its entire catalog, enjoy channels curated by its team of music experts and create their own channel based on a genre, decade and style using our unique Mixer feature. XITE has a full music video catalog through agreements with all major and top independent music labels and distributors, and works to expand this offering every day.  About the role In your role as a Frontend Developer your task will be to bring to life new features, improvements and experiments for the XITE TV app. You’ll be working with Javascript and Lightning framework to transform product ideas into a fantastic user experience. You will be part of an Agile team working to realize the ultimate music video experience for Connected TV and Set-top-boxes. Your team is also a part of a bigger group of fellow frontend developers, who have the focus on React Native and Web development for a TV and Mobile application.

 Responsibilities


 You will be collaborating with the other Engineers to decide on the choices to be made during the development process. You will continuously deliver builds for internal and external tests in order to achieve the user experience that is appropriate for the goals of the project.
 Work closely with our QA team, act on and fix bugs, develop new features and have a big impact on the user experience.
 Assure high quality of deliverables following the best practices.
 Knowledge sharing and progress within the company.


 At least 2 years of working experience with HTML, CSS, JavaScript/Front End Frameworks;
 Good debugging skills and analytical thinking;
 Understanding of good UI/UX;
 Team player with a collaborative attitude;
 You’re obsessed with code quality and committed to making sure everything is well implemented and bug-free;
 Comfortable learning new skills, being proactive and keep up with trends in development world and evolving tech stack;
 Curious and creative;
 Excellent written and oral communication skills in English;
 You live in the Netherlands.


 Our Tech Stack

 JavaScript
 Lightning JS framework

  What working at XITE means Here at XITE we make sure you’re taken care of by providing you the opportunity to develop your career in a young, fast growing and international company. We provide a challenging work environment where you have a lot of autonomy and flexible working hours. We don’t hire assholes! All XITE’ers are different and authentic in their own way, but we all have kindness in common, as well as professionalism and an optimistic attitude. Let’s not forget - we have a passion for good music and good food. That’s why we have chef prepared lunches, Friday afternoon drinks and rooftop parties! Click here to see our benefits.  The process

 1. Apply: Apply for a role and we will contact you. 
2. HR Interview: One of our recruiters will contact you, because we'd really like to find out more about you and to see if there is a culture fit between you and XITE. During this interview you can ask all your questions about the company. 
3. Technical Assignment: This is your moment to shine and let us know what skills you offer! You get one week to make this assignment. Need more time? Not a problem, just let us know! 
4. Technical interview: With two colleagues of XITE we will dive into your Technical assignment. You can also ask all your technical questions to the team! 
5. Offer: Hopefully with our offer we can welcome you to the team of XITE!

 Up for the challenge? Then hit that ‘Apply for this Job’ button!

About Wuunder
Wuunder is a fast-growing, ambitious and above all dynamic scale-up. Every day we turn the market for parcels a bit upside down. We do this by making the process of sending and receiving shipments as simple and as personal as possible. Our secret: a passionate team and the latest technologies. This way we can unburden our customers as much as possible and provide tailor-made solutions. And we go very far in that. We also take care of the customer service of our customers and arrange their transport, warehousing and/or fulfilment with our partners.
Will you become the newest member of Wuunder? Then you will receive from us: 

A versatile position with responsibility and where no day is the same;


A place where you work on your own development;


Room for own initiative and good ideas. We are always open to that. We even encourage it! Whether you work with us for a month or a year;


A work laptop;


Everything else you need to create a nice workplace;


You will also receive a homework allowance (on the days you work at home);


Travel allowance (if you can’t go to work by bike);


A pension scheme;


Holiday allowance (8%);


Money at the end of the month. Between €4000,- and €6000,- gross (bruto) per month, depending on experience.

And what does your role look like at Wuunder?

Coaching and mentoring more junior developers;
Contributing to the architecture of the web platform;
Communicating with other members of the platform development team and the rest of the company to design and implement new functionality in the application;
Improving existing functionality;
Implementing or maintaining API integrations with various shipping providers;
Performing code review and giving feedback to your fellow developers;
Decreasing technical debt and looking at legacy architecture critically;
Working as third line support on a rotating basis (working hours only).

In this role, you will be a core member of the team developing the shipping logistics platform at Wuunder.
Unfortunately we have a few requirements, but don't worry they are easy.

An internet connection so you can work remotely within the EU.


You've mastered the art of the English language.

Our stack: 

Elixir


Phoenix (with lots of liveview)


Postgresql


AWS


Honeycomb


Appsignal

The platform team is self-governing. Our current workflow includes trunk-based development, pairing when appropriate, continuous deployment (sometimes 10+ times per day), and we are open to new innovations. We have a good balance of junior and senior developers in the team.
Some extra information about Wuunder
WORKING FROM HOME
Wuunder has its office in Weert. Yet we call it more of a training location, meeting place or inspiration location. Almost everyone works from home or another location and only comes to Weert one or a few days a month. Good for work-life balance. In this way we limit commuting and we also contribute to CO2 reduction. You have very active contact with other team members on a daily basis. Wuunder now consists of more than 50 people.
WILD AND SELF STARTER
You will have the opportunity to work independently on the growth of Wuunder. In your own field, but always in a team. You work with small, changing teams. We are looking for critical team members who are internally motivated to amaze our customers on a daily basis. We make agreements within those teams. Due to the enormous growth, it is important that you are a self-starter.
INTERNATIONAL TEAM
Wuunder was founded in 2016 in the Netherlands and is now also active in Belgium, Luxembourg and Germany. Our customers are mainly Dutch, German, French and English speaking. Understanding and speaking any of these languages is a plus, but only fluent English is required. Not only do we work internationally, but our team is also international.
Interested? Send us your motivation letter and CV (or a link to your linkedin profile). Then we will contact you as soon as possible!
