Your role as Front-end developerIn this role you will be working on simplifying a traditionally complex service and turning it into an intuitive and worldwide scalable product that enables companies to manage logistics in more time and cost-efficient way. You build on a platform that is growing fast and to which many new features are constantly being added. Together with the team you (pro) actively contribute to the further development of the platform and you are also responsible for the technical future of the platform. Your opinion and ideas really matter at Shypple. The focus of this position is on the user interface, where you will ensure the application is intuitive and works as well as it looks. You will work closely together with analysts, designers, and the actual users of the application.*What you'll bring*

A minimum of 5+ years of relevant work experience with React/Redux;
You love to work with Typescript;
You have experience designing, building and maintaining growing applications;
Good verbal and written communication skills in English;
The ability to learn new things quickly, understand a business and it's product requirements.

You get

A great working environment with a team of talented developers who work together for extraordinary success;
A competitive salary;
Good secondary benefits;
The opportunity to be a part of a great adventure where you can grow, develop and get the best out of yourself, including a yearly budget for personal development and many career growth opportunities;
An office in the heart of Rotterdam with a sunny roof terrace.

We’re proud that “The Shypple way” is increasingly creating interest in the national and international press: Quote, Silicon Canals, M&A* and *De Ondernemer and that our magnificent growth is also recognized by various nominations: named the winner of the Tech5* country award 2021 as hottest scale-up in the Netherlands.*
